						               													<description>An interesting economic game, where players try to become the first player, who could buy and purchase 15-18 goods of 6 different types.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Several taxes and fees must be paid on the way to becoming the winner of the game. A few of them are fixed amounts, which must be paid when a player reaches a certain step on the way up, some must be paid, when a player misses a chance to buy or purchase goods and therefore has to draw 1 of 80 event cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are six different goods available. A player can purchase 1-3 goods of a chosen type depending on a dice throw. Red goods can only be purchased by throwing a 6, green goods need at least a 5, yellow ones a 4 and so on.&amp;#10;All goods cost 10.000 per piece, but the selling price is higher for the harder goods, from 16.000 - 32.000.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Before selling, another dice throw is required, which needs matching  the throws while purchasing the goods.&amp;#10; Last but not least, the purchase and sale of goods can be challenged by other players, if their  bid  was either lower or higher than the agreed on transaction.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
